{
  "texts": [
    "Several studies have been conducted to extract the target signal from originals containing waves from various sources or separate signals and noise (Zhu et al. 2019b; Tibi et al. 2021 Tibi et al., 2022;; Dalai et al. 2021; Novoselov et al. 2022; Yin et al. 2022a; Xu et al. 2022; Wang and Zhang 2023).",
    "These efforts will lead to the effective use of observation data unanalyzed due to a low signal-to-noise ratio.",
    "ML has been applied to estimate site amplification characteristics, of which frequency dependency varies among sites.",
    "Roten and Olsen (2021) developed a DL model to estimate the relative site amplification characteristics between borehole and surface seismograms from discretized S-wave velocity profiles.",
    "Pan et al. (2022) used a DL model to estimate S-wave site amplification characteristics from the information on microtremor HVSR."
  ]
}